Argentine Stocks: Grupo Galicia, Ledesma, Petrobras, Tenaris

-- B y   B r y a n   G i b e l
-- 
2011-08-08T20:38:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-08/argentine-stocks-ledesma-petrobras-argentina-tenaris-tumble.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 4:30 p.m. New York time.  The Merval Index slid 11 percent to 2,738.41, its biggest
one-day decline since October 2008. It was the worst performer
among 91 equity gauges tracked by Bloomberg.  Grupo Financiero Galicia SA (GGAL)  ,  Argentina ’s largest
consumer lender, declined 12 percent to 4.97 pesos, its biggest
drop since October 2008. The price of Argentine dollar-
denominated  government bonds  fell today, which signals lower
value for banks’ fixed-income holdings.  BBVA Banco Frances SA (FRAN) 
, a unit of  Spain ’s Banco Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria SA,
dropped 12 percent to 11.30 pesos, the lowest since September.  Ledesma SAAI (LEDE AF), the Argentine sugar producer, fell
13 percent to 7.10 pesos, its largest decline since October
2008. Raw sugar fell to a five-week low on concern that
commodity demand will ease because of a global slowdown and as
worldwide supplies increase.  Petrobras Argentina SA (PESA)   plummeted 15 percent to
6.97 pesos for its biggest drop since March 2009. Oil fell to an
eight-month low as investors fled commodities for assets such as
Treasury bills and gold after  Standard & Poor’s  downgraded the
U.S.’s credit rating.  Tenaris SA (TEN)  , the world’s largest
producer of seamless steel tubes used in the petroleum and
mechanical industries, fell 12 percent to 70.20 pesos, its
biggest decline since October 2008.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Bryan Gibel in New York at 
 bgibel@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
